history.content: One additional reality check is that nobody at the University of California needs cs162 to graduate. That's the good news.

In @1687, the answer says there are "100 seats left, that will be released to the first 100 people on the waitlist". Is there any priority for processing the waitlist? I'm going to be a super senior and need this class to graduate this semester, but I'm 130 on the waitlist and I'm kind of freaking out. Would have signed up for it earlier, but it conflicted with a time in a different class that I've since dropped.

Thanks!
